# Contour Lab Design System

Follow the Figma file **Contour-Lab-Design** (node 139-869). All tokens live in `src/app/globals.css`. Use CSS variables only; do not hardcode hex values for brand colors or typography.

## Colors

Use these variables for all UI:

| Token | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `var(--color-white)` | #ffffff |
| `var(--color-light-grey)` | #f6f6f6, subtle backgrounds |
| `var(--color-grey)` | #939393, muted text |
| `var(--color-grey-hard)` | #555555, body/secondary text |
| `var(--color-black)` | #141414, primary text |
| `var(--color-red-main)` | #b9040f, primary accent, CTAs, borders |
| `var(--color-red-dark)` | #7b0e23, primary hover/active |
| `var(--color-red-purple)` | #b81b3a |
| `var(--color-header-bg)` | header background |
| `var(--color-hero-bg)` | #f8f8f8, hero section |
| `var(--color-nav-grey)` | #909090 |

**Rules:**
- Buttons (primary): `bg-[var(--color-red-main)]`, hover `var(--color-red-dark)`.
- Outline/ghost: `border-[var(--color-red-main)]`, `text-[var(--color-red-main)]`.
- Body/subtitle text: `var(--color-grey-hard)` or `var(--color-black)` for headings.
- Never use raw `#b9040f` or other hex in components; always use the variable.

## Typography

- **Headings / hero:** `var(--font-sans)` (Gilroy). Use tokens for size:
  - Headline 1: `var(--font-headline-1)` (110px), line `var(--font-headline-1-line)` (100px)
  - Headline 2: 52px, line 1.2
  - Headline 3: 36px, line 1.2
  - Headline 4: 24px, line 1.2
- **UI (buttons, nav, inputs):** `var(--font-inter)` (Inter, weight 400). Use for NavLink, Button, LanguageSelector.
- **Display:** `var(--font-display-1)` (20px), display-2 (20px), display-3 (18px), line 1.3.

Define font in styles: `fontFamily: "var(--font-sans)"` or `"var(--font-inter)"`. Prefer design tokens over arbitrary Tailwind font sizes for consistency.

## Buttons

- **Variants:** `primary` | `secondary` | `outline` | `outlineLight`.
- **Sizes:** `sm` | `md` | `lg` (height 44/48/56px, use `Button` / `PrimaryButton` / `OutlineLightButton` from `@/components/Button`).
- **Icons:** primary → 36px arrow; outline/outlineLight → 30px. Padding differs by variant (see `paddingByVariant` in Button.tsx).
- Always use Inter for button label: `fontFamily: "var(--font-inter)"`.

## Layout

- **Container:** Use `Container` from `@/components/Container` for max-width and horizontal padding (90% / 91.67% / 91.46% at breakpoints).
- **Header:** Sticky, `h-20`, `var(--color-header-bg)`. Desktop: logo + nav + language + CTA; tablet: logo + burger (BurgerToCloseIcon).
- **Hero:** `var(--color-hero-bg)`, min-height 90vh; content left, decorative image right; social icons right edge; scroll indicator bottom center (red circle, white arrow).

## Components to reuse

- `Button`, `PrimaryButton`, `OutlineLightButton` from `@/components/Button`
- `Container` from `@/components/Container`
- `NavLink`, `Logo`, `LanguageSelector` from `@/components/header`
- Hero: `HeroText` from `@/components/hero/HeroText`
- Icons: `ArrowRightIcon`, `ArrowDownIcon`, `BurgerToCloseIcon` from `@/components/icons`

## Do not

- Hardcode brand colors (red, black, greys) in TSX/CSS; use `var(--color-*)`.
- Mix Gilroy and Inter arbitrarily: headings/hero = Gilroy, nav/buttons/forms = Inter.
- Introduce new button variants or sizes without aligning with Figma and existing `Button` API.
